The paper deals with the problem of broadcasting a single message in a dynamic radio network, which involves distributed algorithms and graph-based models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves network connectivity, communication complexity, and information theory, which are relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also deals with adaptive adversaries and stability properties, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
